ne comment POST fails, but summary includes it anyway. Need to actually post comments (or test against a realistic mock that tracks state) to catch this.\n\n**Behavior 5: Full sequence end-to-end** — Orchestration failures: read PR succeeds, inline comments post, but summary fails and is never posted. Or timeouts, rate limiting, API version incompatibilities. System-level testing of real GitHub APIs is needed. If the analysis step (behavior 3) is Agentic, then multiple agentic steps in sequence makes this Workflow."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13519,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13519},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18411f30-851f-4df3-a25f-3d3f0e8104af","uuid":"a9bb2fff-f1bf-4b5a-a17d-c6311a54a7a0"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01DLAdXZ3xvLK1beYnBksKyJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01D6tDYBkU6sZfx6p29UjBih","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Unit tests with mocked diffs could pass while real GitHub diffs cause filtering failures due to format edge cases (off-by-one line numbers, hunk boundaries, context lines). Real failure: the analyzer includes unchanged lines or misses changed lines because the filtering logic makes incorrect assumptions about diff format. Testing with realistic GitHub diff format (fixture or API response) is required to catch line-mapping boundary errors.","test_description":"Create a PR with multiple files and multiple changed regions per file. Verify the analysis result includes only the changed line ranges and does not analyze unchanged regions. Compare actual change ranges (from diff) against lines included in analysis findings.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Unit tests mocking the GitHub API will not catch subtle failures in line number mapping. GitHub's API requires specific commit/path/line parameters, and the meaning of 'line' differs between unified diff format and GitHub's diff view. Real failures include: off-by-one calculation of diff line numbers, incorrect mapping between original/modified file line numbers, or mishandling of context vs. changed lines. Testing against realistic GitHub diff structure (API fixtures or real API) is needed to verify correct positioning.","test_description":"Post a review comment for a specific changed line and verify it appears on that exact line in GitHub's PR diff view, not on a neighboring unchanged line or wrong file. Test edge cases: first/last line of diff, multi-hunk files, and range comments if supported.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.5,"System":0.25,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This tests the core analysis capability. If the analyzer is deterministic (rule-based static analysis), Integration is sufficient—tests verify the detection logic works. If the analyzer is non-deterministic (LLM-based), mocking the LLM hides real detection failures and Agentic becomes necessary. Without certainty of implementation, Integration is the practical minimum that catches deterministic failures. However, if the system uses an LLM, only Agentic testing exposes actual analysis capability. Real failure: detection logic misses or misclassifies the injected bug.","test_description":"Create a PR with a known injected bug (e.g., unhandled null pointer, missing input validation, incorrect error handling). Run the PR review system and verify that at least one finding identifies the bug. The finding should accurately describe the defect, not just vague suggestions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Will catch rule-based detection failures reliably; Agentic tests needed if system uses LLM analysis.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.4,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.3,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to an inline comment that was also posted — no findings appear in the summary without a matching inline comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":